<HEADLINE>
`GINGERBREAD MAN' BLAND; `PEACEKEEPER' JUST SAVED 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES:  &UR; ``The Gingerbread Man''  &LR; _ Director Robert
Altman's improvisational style and writer John Grisham's plotting
would seem to make for a solid marriage. Not so. This rambling
mystery starring Kenneth Branagh _ not to be confused with the J.P.
Donleavy book _ goes nowhere, slowly.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``The Peacekeeper''  &LR; _ No, not the one with George Clooney _
that's ``Peacemaker.'' Dolph Lundgren stars here, as the one guy
who can save the world from nuclear anni-hilation. The erstwhile
action star is getting a little old for all this stuff, falling
behind Stallone and Van Damme in the macho standings. Only Roy
Scheider and Montel Williams in supporting roles save this disaster
film from, well, disaster.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``Dead Heart''  &LR; _ Brian Brown, in one of his finest
performances, portrays an Australian lawman caught in a cultural
crossfire. Complex and challenging, which makes it different from
so many other films released this year. Perhaps the beginning of
another Australian renaissance.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC;
</P>
<P>
   DVD UPDATE: ``The Sweet Hereafter,'' now available on digital
video disc, features knowledgeable, insightful commentary from
novelist Russell Banks and director Atom Egoyan on the
transformation from book to film. ... Walt Disney will release its
first animated title on DVD with the direct-to-video release of
``Beauty and the Beast: The Enchanted Christmas'' on Oct. 13. ...
The DVD for ``Boogie Nights'' contains nine scenes deleted from the
theatrical release, along with extensive biographies of the cast
and crew.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS:  &UR; July 31:  &LR; ``Cousin Cousine.'' &UR; Aug. 4:
 &LR; ``Jackie Brown,'' ``The Wedding Singer,'' ``Deceiver,'' ``Meet the
Deedles,'' ``Quick Silver Highway,'' ``Preston Sturges
Collection,'' ``Blues Brothers 2000,'' ``The Swan Princess II.''
 &UR; Aug. 11:  &LR; ``The Man in the Iron Mask,'' ``Mr. Nice Guy,''
``Senseless,'' ``1776,'' ``John and Julie,'' ``I Love You, I Love
You Not,'' ``Godspell,'' ``Three for the Show,'' ``The Informant,''
``The Big Lebowski,'' ``Mr. Nice Guy,'' ``The Substitute 2:
School's Out,'' ``Elvis Meets Nixon,'' ``Hamsun,'' ``Merlin.''
 &UR; Aug. 18:  &LR; ``The Apostle,'' ``Kundun,'' ``An Alan Smithee Film:
Burn Hollywood Burn,'' ``A Sunday in the Country,'' ``The
Clockmaker,'' ``Summer Fling,'' ``The Borrowers.''  &UR; Aug. 25:  &LR; ``Men
with Guns,'' ``The Last Way Out,'' ``Sub Down,'' ``Naked Lies.''
 &UR; Sept. 1:  &LR; ``Titanic.''  &UR; Sept. 15:  &LR; ``Lady and the Tramp,'' ``The
Last Don II.''
