<HEADLINE>
WHEN YOU GO: COSTA RICA 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  c.1998 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Room rates for Tabacon Lodge are $85 for the high season and $75
for the rainy or green season, which is May through June and
September through November. Rates, which are expected to increase
later this year, include breakfast and unlimited access to the
resort's hot springs.
</P>
<P>
   If you are not staying at the lodge, the day rate for the spa
and hot springs is $14 ($7 for children).
</P>
<P>
   Call 011-506-256-1500 or e-mail tabacon(at)sol.racsa.co.cr.
</P>
<P>
   _ Room rates for Hotel La Garza are about $70 a night. Meals are
not included and it should be noted that there are few dining
options in the area other than the hotel's open-air restaurant.
</P>
<P>
   Call 011-506-475-5222 or e-mail lagarza(at)sol.racsa.co.cr.
</P>
<P>
   _ For general Costa Rican tourist information, call 800-343-6332
or visit the Web site: www.tourism-costarica.com.
</P>
