<P>
   &UR; USING THE ARTS TO STIMULATE INTELLECTUAL GROWTH &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (1,600 words) &QL; 
 &UR; By RALPH BLUMENTHAL &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; From Family Circle magazine &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Music, art and drama can pay huge intellectual dividends in
terms of a child's mental development, Blumenthal writes. Studies
have shown, for example, that students who study music do better on
their SATs and score higher on spatial IQ tests. Blumenthal offers
tips on how parents can boost their children's learning powers
through exposure to the arts. (slugged:
BC-ARTS-STIMULATE-IQ-(BACK-TO-SCHOOL)-NYTSF, priority code r,
category code l)
