<P>
   &UR; IS MY CHILD READY FOR KINDERGARTEN? &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (1,500 words) &QL; 
 &UR; By LESLIE BULION &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; From Child magazine &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Parents of children with late-summer or fall birthdays often
find themselves faced with a difficult decision _ whether to let
the child be one of the youngest in the kindergarten class, or wait
until the following year. Bulion tells the stories of three
families confronted with this dilemma and how they reached their
decisions. (slugged:
BC-KINDERGARTEN-READINESS-(BACK-TO-SCHOOL)-NYTSF, priority code r,
category code l)
