   &UR; ARE FAMILY-FRIENDLY POLICIES UNFAIR TO THE CHILDLESS &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (1,500 words) &QL; 
 &UR; By DIANE HARRIS &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; From Working Mother magazine &QL;
</P>
<P>
   More and more businesses are adopting policies that recognize
the problems parents have balancing work and family. But now these
family-friendly policies are igniting a backlash from childless
employees who feel resentful about what they perceive as more
favorable treatment of working parents. Harris looks at the
validity of these objections and suggests ways that employers can
treat both groups equitably. (slugged:
BC-CHILDLESS-WORKER-BACKLASH-(BACK-TO-SCHOOL)-NYTSF, priority code
r, category code l) &QL;
