 &UR; From Kiwanis magazine &QL;
</P>
<P>
   High-fat diets and sedentary lifestyles are leading an
increasing number of children to tip the scales at far beyond their
ideal weight. Hours of playing videogames or watching television
instead of partaking in more physical activities are taking their
toll, Downey says. So is the decline of the family dinner hour.
Downey offers advice to parents on how to help children take off
those extra pounds. (slugged:
BC-CHILDHOOD-OBESITY-(BACK-TO-SCHOOL)-NYTSF, priority code r,
category code l) &QL;
