   EDs: To move by 4:30 p.m. EDT.
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   SHOOTINGS-MEMORIALS _ WASHINGTON _ Lawmakers set aside
legislative business Monday to offer tributes to the two U.S.
Capitol Police officers killed Friday by a gunman. There were
emotional tributes from members of the House and Senate as both
chambers prepared to attend a memorial service on Tuesday in the
Capitol Rotunda for the fallen lawmen. (Harlan, Cox News Service.)
</P>
<P>
   with (Developing) AUS-CHESNUT-DAUGHTERS _ Trying to talk with
daughters of slain capitol officer J.J. Chestnut. The daughters
live here in Austin. (Tanamachi, Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-LEWINSKY _ WASHINGTON _ (Developing) President Clinton's
lawyers are searching for a compromise with special prosecutor
Kenneth Starr that would spare the president from having to testify
before a grand jury _ possibly as early as Tuesday _ in the Monica
Lewinsky matter. (Deans, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   POWERBALL _ DAYTON, Ohio _ Even though the odds are 80 million
to 1, everybody's talking about the $250 million powerball jackpot.
Big Red's Liquors in Richmond Ind. has increased it Powerball
machines from four to seven to handle the crush of people from
Kentucky and Ohio expected to stand in line for hours for a ticket.
By 9:15 a.m., his parking lot was already full. (Kumar, Dayton
Daily News)
</P>
<P>
   GM _ DAYTON, Ohio _ We're closer to settlement to the strikes in
Flint and might have a deal that prevents a strike in Dayton.
(Wagner, Dayton Daily News)
</P>
<P>
   DDN-COX-PRISON _ DAYTON, Ohio _ Gov. George Voinovich wants to
move to shut down the private prison in Ohio. He says they've lied
to the state, and violated their charter about types of prisoners _
they're housing: miximum security folks in a medium security
prison. (Miller, Dayton Daily News)
</P>
<P>
   BAXTER-COLUMN _ ATLANTA _ On likely Ga. Democratic gubernatorial
nominee Roy Barnes and his ``Lemme tell you somethin'' folksy
manner, and how it'll play in the fall election. (Baxter, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   HEAT_ DALLAS _ A look at coping skills of Texans as they head
into the 22nd consecutive day of highs above 100. Dallas today had
a low temperature of 83. It's the 25th day in a row _ a record _
that the low was more than 80. (Rochell, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   AUS-AIRPORT _ Four months after they announced recommendations
for companies to run new airport concessions, leading to all bids
being thrown out, the city is making the announcements again and we
hear it's awfully familiar. The airport staff is suggesting again
that the city hire Paradies Shops and CA One to handle most of the
retail at Austin-Bergstrom. Paradies was part of the reason for
last time's re-bid: the city staff neglected to mention to the
airport advisory board and city council that the company had a
troubled past including indictments for fraud and bribery in
Atlanta. (Hiott, Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
