of Tuesday, July 28 and thereafter. The stories will carry the
``f'' financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For
questions about stories, contact Stewart Slavin at the Daily News,
(818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   INTERNET-STOCK-NOVICES (Los Angeles) _ When Livina Goodrow heard
about CitySearch, an Internet company, she called her broker to buy
the stock. But in her haste, she took a wrong turn on the
information superhighway. CitySearch, which soon is going public,
will use the ticker symbol CTYS. In the meantime, another company,
Cityscape Financial, is using the same symbol. She mistakenly
bought 3,000 shares of Cityscape at 12 and 22 cents a share.
Unfortunately, Cityscape is on the verge of bankruptcy. She's just
the latest example of the dangers of mixing Internet stock hype
with novice investors. By Deborah Adamson.
</P>
<P>
   GODZILLA-VIDEO (Los Angeles) _ ``Godzilla,'' who helped wreck
the second quarter for several companies, hits home video shelves
in early November. Watch out Blockbuster. By Dave McNary.
</P>
<P>
   LLOYD-COLUMN (Los Angeles) _ Let the hire beware. Daily News
columnist Ken Lloyd, Ph.D., a specialist in organizational
behavior, answers readers' questions on workplace ethics and
relationships.
</P>
</TEXT>
