<SLUG> BC-WELFARE-EMPLOYERS-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
STUDY SHOWS MOST EMPLOYERS SATISFIED IN HIRING WELFARE RECIPIENTS 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (EDs: FILED in ``w'' and ``f'' categories)   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By NICOLE TSONG  
 c.1998 Hearst Newspapers  
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ Most employers who hire former welfare recipients
are satisfied with their work, but a majority of the workers get
low pay and few benefits, according to two reports released Monday
by the Urban Institute, a Washington-based think tank.
</P>
<P>
   Seventy percent of the employers who have hired people on
