welfare are part-time.
</P>
<P>
   ``These are people still living on the edge,'' Meyer said.
``They are quite vulnerable.''
</P>
<P>
   The combination of low wages and no or few health benefits is
still a problem for former welfare recipients, even though a large
number of employers are willing to hire them, he added.
</P>
<P>
   The Urban Institute's report said only half of the firms that
