<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Braves on deck: Cincinnati Reds
 &HT;    By Thomas Stinson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   _ When: 7:05 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   _ Where: Cinergy Field.
</P>
<P>
   _ TV: Fox Sports South.
</P>
<P>
   _ Probable starting pitchers: RHP Kevin Millwood (11-5, 4.19;
first appearance vs. Reds) vs. RHP Pete Harnisch (7-5, 3.32; 6-8,
3.11 lifetime vs. Braves).
</P>
<P>
   _ Notes: One of the few pleasant aspects to this woeful
Cincinnati season has been the resurgence of Pete Harnisch's
career. After a horrible 1997 that included more than four months
on the disabled list because of anxiety and insomnia and his
release by Milwaukee during the winter, Harnisch has rebounded to
become the Reds' most consistent starter. While he is 1-4 in his
last seven starts, he has maintained a sub-3.50 ERA since May.
Until he gave up six earned runs at Colorado in his last start,
Harnisch had a string of 16 games in which he allowed three earned
runs or less. His record has been hurt by Cincinnati's laggard
offense, which has scored one run behind him in six of his 16
games. After several weeks of unsteady work, Millwood is starting
on five days of rest for the second time this month, and although
he is 1-1 in his last two starts, he has recovered from some rocky
work in mid-June. After giving up 12 runs in two games against
Montreal (June 19) and the New York Yankees (June 24), Millwood has
allowed just five runs in his last 23 innings (1.96 ERA).
Cincinnati is one of two teams, along with Houston, that Millwood
has yet to face in his career. In his debut against five clubs this
season, he has gone 3-1.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
