<HEADLINE>
BY DESIGN: AIR-CONDITIONED DRESSES 
</HEADLINE>
  (lb) 
 By ANNE-MARIE SCHIRO   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Sportswear may be fashion's preference for fall, but
for summer many women prefer the ease of a dress that bares the
arms and neck.
</P>
<P>
   Henri Bendel has strapless Liberty prints by Madison Brown
($100) and solid linen slip dresses in many colors by Geronimo
($140). Sundresses in solid black or dark florals ($48 to $59) can
be found at Sisley, 469 West Broadway (Prince Street).
</P>
<P>
   Macy's has CK Calvin Klein's leaf-print tank dress ($275),
Emanuel's V-neck brown shift ($298) and Tahari's V-neck charcoal
jersey ($330).
</P>
<P>
   Black dresses by DKNY in several lengths with different
necklines ($99 to $255) and Tocca's embroidered powder-blue
sundresses ($200) are at Neiman Marcus. Saks Fifth Avenue has a
brown wrap dress by Max Mara ($475), a multicolored striped knit
sundress from Ralph by Ralph Lauren ($375) and a long striped knit
tank dress from Oscar by Oscar de la Renta ($298).
</P>
</TEXT>
