7-27 -- Dr. Marvin Minsky, one of the leading theorists of
artificial intelligence, at his home in Brookline. In the late
1950s, Minsky, 71, and a collaborator founded a research program
that would evolve into the MIT Artificial Intelligence Laboratory.
