<TEXT>
<P>
   ATTENTION EDITORS: The following photos are part of tonight's
New York Times Photo Package, moving 7/27/98. Photo clients will
automatically receive these photos via AP's PhotoExpress or may
download them from either the Wieck Photo Database in Dallas at
972-392-0888 or from NYTPhotos on Newscom at 305-448-8411.
Non-clients can make individual purchases by calling 212-556-4204.
</P>
<P>
   (NYT18) NEWARK, N.J. -- July 27, 1998 --
NJ-PROSTITUTES-PORTELLA, 7-27 -- Newark Police Capt. Louis Portella
Jr., who is investigating the slayings of 14 prostitutes, has
gained the confidence of streetwalkers like Soft Touch. While
investigators need the invaluable information that only these women
can provide and sometimes turn a blind eye to their soliciting,
they cannot afford to give the appearance of shielding the
prostitutes, whose very occupations violate the law. ``The most
important thing you can give these women is your word,'' he says.
(Norman Y. Lono/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT17) WINSTED, Conn. -- July 27, 1998 -- NADER-MUSEUM, 7-27 --
Fred Hyde and Ralph Nader's sister Laura at the old factory where
they hope to open the Museum of American Tort Law. Nader, Winsted's
