SWEEPSTAKES-ELDERLY-I-2, 7-27 -- Dorothy Edouart, an 88-year-old
widow, has played magazine sweepstakes and similar promotions
passionately for years. Her family estimates that in five years she
spent $60,000 on magazines she never read and merchandise she never
used, without winning a dime. Now, she is suing her son for the
right to sell the family's estate, saying she needs more money for
sweepstakes. The family is seeking to have her declared
incompetent. (Bill Powers/New York Times Photo)
